body:
It is my understanding of the LRM that the following module should write "ping". This is also what happens with Xilinx XSim and Mentor Modelsim. 

```
module top;
  reg clk = 1;
  always @(posedge clk) $display("ping");
endmodule
```

But Icarus Verilog (917d754, todays git head) does not produce any output when running this design. Even worse, the following slightly larger design does print "pong" but not "ping":

```
module top;
  reg clk = 1;
  pong pong_inst (.clk(clk));
  always @(posedge clk) $display("ping");
endmodule

module pong(input clk);
  always @(posedge clk) $display("pong");
endmodule
```

As you might be able to imagine, there are some cases where it can have quite confusing consequences if different parts of a verification environment disagree about the number of clock edges since simulation start.

